SKILL|architecture-diagram|"Dark-themed SVG architecture/cloud/infra diagrams as HTML."
STEP|1|Best suited for:**
STEP|2|Software system architecture (frontend / backend / database layers)
STEP|3|Cloud infrastructure (VPC, regions, subnets, managed services)
STEP|4|Microservice / service-mesh topology
STEP|5|Database + API map, deployment diagrams
STEP|6|Anything with a tech-infra subject that fits a dark, grid-backed aesthetic
STEP|7|Look elsewhere first for:**
STEP|8|Physics, chemistry, math, biology, or other scientific subjects
STEP|9|Physical objects (vehicles, hardware, anatomy, cross-sections)
STEP|10|Floor plans, narrative journeys, educational / textbook-style visuals
STEP|11|Hand-drawn whiteboard sketches (consider `excalidraw`)
STEP|12|Animated explainers (consider an animation skill)
STEP|13|User describes their system architecture (components, connections, technologies)
STEP|14|Generate the HTML file following the design system below
STEP|15|Save with `write_file` to a `.html` file (e.g. `~/architecture-diagram.html`)
STEP|16|User opens in any browser — works offline, no dependencies
STEP|17|/[project-name]-architecture.html
STEP|18|**Font:** JetBrains Mono (Monospace), loaded from Google Fonts
STEP|19|**Sizes:** 12px (Names), 9px (Sublabels), 8px (Annotations), 7px (Tiny labels)
STEP|20|**Background:** Slate-950 (`#020617`) with a subtle 40px grid pattern
STEP|21|Draw an opaque background rect (`#0f172a`)
STEP|22|Draw the semi-transparent styled rect on top
STEP|23|**Z-Order:** Draw arrows *early* in the SVG (after the grid) so they render behind component boxes
STEP|24|**Arrowheads:** Defined via SVG markers
STEP|25|**Security Flows:** Use dashed lines in rose color (`#fb7185`)
STEP|26|**Boundaries:**
STEP|27|**Standard Height:** 60px (Services); 80-120px (Large components)
STEP|28|**Vertical Gap:** Minimum 40px between components
STEP|29|**Message Buses:** Must be placed *in the gap* between services, not overlapping them
STEP|30|**Legend Placement:** **CRITICAL.** Must be placed outside all boundary boxes. Calculate the lowest Y-coordinate of all boundaries and place the legend at least 20px below it.
STEP|31|**Header:** Title with a pulsing dot indicator and subtitle
STEP|32|**Main SVG:** The diagram contained within a rounded border card
STEP|33|**Summary Cards:** A grid of three cards below the diagram for high-level details
STEP|34|**Footer:** Minimal metadata
STEP|35|**Single File:** One self-contained `.html` file
STEP|36|**No External Dependencies:** All CSS and SVG must be inline (except Google Fonts)
STEP|37|**No JavaScript:** Use pure CSS for any animations (like pulsing dots)
STEP|38|**Compatibility:** Must render correctly in any modern web browser
PIT|Best suited for:**
PIT|Software system architecture (frontend / backend / database layers)
PIT|Cloud infrastructure (VPC, regions, subnets, managed services)
PIT|Microservice / service-mesh topology
PIT|Database + API map, deployment diagrams
PIT|Anything with a tech-infra subject that fits a dark, grid-backed aesthetic
